-- Deripaska’s Basic Element Sees $3 Billion in Construction Sales
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-03-26T12:57:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/deripaska-s-basic-element-sees-3-billion-in-construction-sales.html
Russian billionaire  Oleg
Deripaska ’s Basic Element holding company expects 90 billion
rubles ($3.1 billion) of sales from its construction division
this year.  The unit’s businesses include home building, development,
infrastructure provision and cement, the company said in the
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
